Hey everyone! :bobross:
I'm running into an issue with a Forms API call and I'd like to see if anyone here can help.

*Issue:*
Form API submissions are submitting to the correlated HubSpot form successfully, but are being tagged as bot activity ("Submission from bot activity" shown on each submission), hiding those submissions from the total submissions count on the form's Details view.

*Details:*
We're working on a form submission API call set up with C# (using RestSharp) from their SPA -- the submission currently includes an empty hutk value, and valid values for the ipAddress, pageUri, and pageName params.

The hutk value is empty as we've removed the tracking code from their SPA for the time being.

*What we've tried:*
Support had suggested it was identified as bot activity because we didn't include the ipAddress in the context object originally, but upon making that update our test submissions still included the "Submission from bot activity" tag.

*Code:*
```{
    public class HubSpotService : IHubSpotService
    {
        private readonly IApplicationPrincipal _principal;
        private readonly IOptions&lt;AnalyticsSettings&gt; _configuration;
        private readonly IRestClient _client;

        public HubSpotService(IOptions&lt;AnalyticsSettings&gt; configuration)
        {
            _configuration = configuration;

            _client = new RestClient("<https://api.hsforms.com/submissions/v3/>");
            _client.AddDefaultHeader("content-type", "application/json");
            _client.AddDefaultHeader("accept", "application/json");
            _client.AddDefaultQueryParameter("hapikey", _configuration.Value.ApiKey);

        }

        public async Task&lt;Response&gt; CreateContact(string firstName, string lastName, string email, string company, string phone, string htk, string ipAddress)
        {
            var request = new RestRequest("integration/submit/{portalId}/{formId}", <http://Method.POST|Method.POST>);
            request.AddUrlSegment("portalId", _configuration.Value.Portal);
            request.AddUrlSegment("formId", _configuration.Value.RegistrationFormId);

            request.AddJsonBody(new
            {
                fields = new List&lt;object&gt;(){
                    new {
                        name = "email",
                        value = email
                    },
                    new {
                        name = "company",
                        value = company
                    },
                    new {
                        name = "phone",
                        value = phone
                    },
                    new {
                        name = "firstname",
                        value = firstName
                    },
                    new {
                        name = "lastname",
                        value = lastName
                    }
                },
                context = new {
                    hutk = htk,
                    pageUri = "<http://example-app.com/#registration>",
                    pageName = "Sign Up",
                    ipAddress = ipAddress ?? ""
                }
            });

            return await _client.PostAsync&lt;Response&gt;(request);
        }

    }
}```
I'm not too familiar with C#/RestSharp, and haven't been able to confidently identify any issues with the code above. The only thing I can think of is that the User-Agent may not be set in the RestSharp client appropriately (though I do not know if that's necessary), which I imagine could cause the calls to appear to be from a bot on HubSpot's end.

If anyone has any thoughts here I'd appreciate the input - thank you!
